1
00:00:07,925 --> 00:00:09,134
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

2
00:00:09,176 --> 00:00:11,846
<i>HOSHI: Enterprise</i> 
to<i> Shuttlepod 1.</i>

3
00:00:14,682 --> 00:00:17,726
<i>Enterprise</i> to<i> Shuttlepod 1.</i>

4
00:00:17,768 --> 00:00:21,438
Captain Archer, please respond.

5
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:24,942
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> TO<i> SHUTTLEPOD 1.</i>

6
00:00:24,984 --> 00:00:27,987
CAPTAIN ARCHER, PLEASE RESPOND.

7
00:00:29,697 --> 00:00:30,990
LIEUTENANT?

8
00:00:31,031 --> 00:00:33,575
THEY TOOK SOME WEAPONS FIRE.

9
00:00:33,617 --> 00:00:35,536
MAIN POWER'S OFFLINE.

10
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:39,414
GRAVITY PLATING, LIFE SUPPORT.

11
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:40,666
BIOSIGNS?

12
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:43,084
NONE.

13
00:00:46,839 --> 00:00:51,468
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

14
00:00:51,510 --> 00:00:54,638
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

15
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:58,475
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

16
00:00:58,517 --> 00:01:02,187
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

17
00:01:02,229 --> 00:01:06,608
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

18
00:01:06,650 --> 00:01:10,278
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

19
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:13,782
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

20
00:01:13,824 --> 00:01:17,118
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

21
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:19,496
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

22
00:01:19,538 --> 00:01:22,082
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

23
00:01:22,123 --> 00:01:24,835
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

24
00:01:24,877 --> 00:01:29,673
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

25
00:01:29,715 --> 00:01:32,676
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

26
00:01:32,718 --> 00:01:37,389
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

27
00:01:37,431 --> 00:01:40,267
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

28
00:01:40,308 --> 00:01:46,273
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

29
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:47,608
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

30
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:49,985
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

31
00:01:50,027 --> 00:01:53,989
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

32
00:01:54,031 --> 00:01:58,118
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

33
00:02:16,261 --> 00:02:18,931
<i>ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S STARLOG,</i>
<i>SUPPLEMENTAL.</i>

34
00:02:18,973 --> 00:02:20,975
TRIP AND I HAVE LEFT KETO-ENOL,
<i>WHERE WE HAD</i>

35
00:02:21,016 --> 00:02:24,061
<i>A SUCCESSFUL FIRST CONTACT</i>
<i>WITH THE ENOLIANS.</i>

36
00:02:24,103 --> 00:02:27,982
<i>WE ALSO FOUND TIME</i>
<i>TO SQUEEZE IN A LITTLE R&amp;R.</i>

37
00:02:28,023 --> 00:02:30,818
HOSHI: THERE'S ONLY
ONE MORE LOG ENTRY AFTER THAT.

38
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:33,112
SOMETHING ABOUT A PAN ZAN MATCH.

39
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:34,404
PAN ZAN?

40
00:02:34,446 --> 00:02:35,990
IT'S A SPORTING EVENT.

41
00:02:36,031 --> 00:02:38,325
THE CAPTAIN SAID IT WAS
THE CLOSEST THING TO WATER POLO

42
00:02:38,366 --> 00:02:41,036
HE'D SEEN SINCE WE LEFT EARTH.

43
00:02:41,078 --> 00:02:42,830
SENSOR LOGS?

44
00:02:42,871 --> 00:02:44,832
TOO BADLY DAMAGED
TO BE MUCH HELP.

45
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:48,710
IF I MAY, I'VE BEEN RUNNING
A FORENSIC ANALYSIS.

46
00:02:48,752 --> 00:02:52,673
THERE ARE TRACES OF HUMAN BLOOD
ON THE DECK AND BULKHEADS --

47
00:02:52,714 --> 00:02:55,174
BOTH THE CAPTAIN'S
AND COMMANDER TUCKER'S.

48
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:57,845
LIEUTENANT REED
BELIEVES THEY WERE ABDUCTED.

49
00:02:57,886 --> 00:03:02,307
IF THEY WERE, THEY DIDN'T
GO WITHOUT A FIGHT.

50
00:03:04,810 --> 00:03:07,896
SET A COURSE FOR KETO-ENOL.

51
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:23,620
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

52
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:50,438
CAPTAIN.

53
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,900
ARE YOU IN CHARGE HERE?

54
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:56,195
IF YOU'RE NOT, I NEED TO SPEAK
TO YOUR SUPERIOR OFFICER.

55
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,031
[ GRUNTING ]

56
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:05,704
CAPTAIN.

57
00:04:07,581 --> 00:04:09,833
ARCHER: I'M OKAY.

58
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:12,086
MAN: I'D STAY QUIET
IF I WERE YOU.

59
00:04:12,127 --> 00:04:14,713
THE GUARDS DON'T LIKE QUESTIONS.

60
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,637
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE THEY'RE TAKING US?

61
00:04:25,099 --> 00:04:27,475
I HEARD SOMETHING ABOUT CANAMAR.

62
00:04:27,517 --> 00:04:30,270
I ASSUME THAT'S
WHERE WE'RE GOING.

63
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:32,940
ALIEN: IT'S A PENAL COLONY.

64
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:37,819
IS THIS HOW
YOUR JUSTICE SYSTEM WORKS?

65
00:04:37,861 --> 00:04:39,487
SHIP PEOPLE OFF TO PRISON
WITHOUT A TRIAL?

66
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:41,240
THERE'S A PROCESSING STATION
IN ORBIT.

67
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:44,576
YOU'LL BE TRIED, SENTENCED,
AND SENT DOWN TO THE SURFACE.

68
00:04:44,618 --> 00:04:46,120
WHAT IF YOU'RE NOT GUILTY?

69
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:48,872
WE'RE ALL GUILTY
AS FAR AS THEY'RE CONCERNED.

70
00:04:50,207 --> 00:04:52,000
WHY DID THEY TAKE YOU?

71
00:04:53,043 --> 00:04:54,544
THEY THINK WE'RE SMUGGLERS.

72
00:04:54,586 --> 00:04:57,505
I WOULDN'T WANT
TO BE ACCUSED OF SMUGGLING.

73
00:04:57,547 --> 00:05:00,092
THEY'LL PROBABLY
MAKE AN EXAMPLE OF YOU.

74
00:05:17,192 --> 00:05:19,611
WE'RE ON AN EXPLORATORY MISSION.

75
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:22,239
WE BELIEVE OUR CAPTAIN
AND CHIEF ENGINEER

76
00:05:22,281 --> 00:05:24,783
WERE ABDUCTED
AFTER VISITING YOUR PLANET.

77
00:05:24,825 --> 00:05:26,827
<i>ABDUCTED BY WHOM?</i>

78
00:05:26,868 --> 00:05:28,411
WE DON'T KNOW.

79
00:05:28,453 --> 00:05:31,248
<i>WE'RE THE BUSIEST</i>
<i>TRADING OUTPOST IN THIS SYSTEM.</i>

80
00:05:31,290 --> 00:05:34,417
<i>WE GET THOUSANDS OF VISITORS</i>
<i>EVERY DAY.</i>

81
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:35,710
<i>UNFORTUNATELY, THAT ATTRACTS</i>

82
00:05:35,752 --> 00:05:37,629
<i>JUST AS MANY THIEVES</i>
<i>AND SMUGGLERS.</i>

83
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:41,842
<i>AS YOU MIGHT IMAGINE,</i>
<i>MY OFFICERS ARE KEPT</i>
<i>QUITE BUSY.</i>

84
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:44,178
<i>I WISH I COULD HELP YOU.</i>

85
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:46,429
LET US SEND YOU
THEIR DESCRIPTIONS.

86
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:47,722
PERHAPS YOU COULD FIND OUT

87
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:51,018
IF ANY OF YOUR OFFICERS
HAVE SEEN THEM.

88
00:06:20,922 --> 00:06:23,550
ANYTHING ELSE ON THE MENU?

89
00:06:26,594 --> 00:06:29,306
ALIEN: IF YOU DON'T LIKE IT,
GIVE IT TO ME.

90
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:35,520
I LIKE IT JUST FINE.

91
00:06:39,191 --> 00:06:40,692
GIVE IT TO ME.

92
00:06:47,199 --> 00:06:49,076
EAT YOUR OWN.

93
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:52,371
YOU DON'T LISTEN TOO WELL.

94
00:06:52,411 --> 00:06:54,748
THEN WHY DON'T YOU
SAVE YOURSELF THE TROUBLE

95
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:56,457
AND STOP TALKING TO ME?

96
00:07:00,295 --> 00:07:01,546
[ GROWLS ]

97
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:04,341
[ GRUNTS ]

98
00:07:04,383 --> 00:07:05,759
[ GROANS ]

99
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:12,807
THANKS.

100
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:16,186
[ GRUNTS ]

101
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:25,279
YOU SHOULD BE CAREFUL
WITH THE NAUSICAANS.

102
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,030
NASTY TEMPERS.

103
00:07:28,531 --> 00:07:31,492
THANKS FOR THE ADVICE.

104
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:34,037
WHAT WERE YOU SMUGGLING?

105
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:37,457
LATINUM?
ENOLIAN SPICE WINE?

106
00:07:37,498 --> 00:07:39,418
WE'RE NOT SMUGGLERS.

107
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:42,712
I'M THE CHIEF ENGINEER OF
A STARSHIP, AND HE'S MY CAPTAIN.

108
00:07:42,754 --> 00:07:46,174
CAPTAIN OF A STARSHIP.

109
00:07:46,216 --> 00:07:47,884
INTERESTING.

110
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:52,013
I SHOULD HAVE TRIED THAT
WHEN THEY TOOK ME.

111
00:07:52,055 --> 00:07:53,514
IT MIGHT HAVE HELPED.

112
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:56,977
"CAPTAIN ZOUMAS."

113
00:08:15,412 --> 00:08:17,789
A PATROL SHIP INTERCEPTED
THEIR SHUTTLE

114
00:08:17,831 --> 00:08:20,334
AS IT WAS LEAVING ORBIT.

115
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:21,626
T'POL: WHERE ARE THEY?

116
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:23,337
ON BOARD ONE OF OUR TRANSPORTS.

117
00:08:23,378 --> 00:08:25,546
THEY WERE CARRYING
WHAT APPEARED TO BE CONTRABAND,

118
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:27,382
SO THEY WERE TAKEN INTO CUSTODY.

119
00:08:27,424 --> 00:08:30,885
ARE YOUR PATROLS IN THE HABIT
OF ARRESTING INNOCENT PEOPLE?

120
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:33,054
SMUGGLING IS RAMPANT
IN THIS SYSTEM.

121
00:08:33,096 --> 00:08:35,890
MY MEN HAVE ORDERS
TO BOARD UNFAMILIAR VESSELS.

122
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:37,851
MISTAKES CAN BE MADE.

123
00:08:37,892 --> 00:08:40,937
YOU CERTAINLY MADE ONE
THIS TIME.

124
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:43,773
I'VE CONTACTED THE TRANSPORT.
THEY'RE EXPECTING YOU.

125
00:08:43,815 --> 00:08:45,525
THESE ARE THE COORDINATES.

126
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:47,402
I TRUST YOU'LL ACCOMPANY US

127
00:08:47,444 --> 00:08:50,655
TO ENSURE THERE ARE
NO FURTHER MISTAKES.

128
00:08:58,038 --> 00:09:00,207
TUCKER: WHAT IF<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
<i>DOESN'T FIND THE SHUTTLEPOD?</i>

129
00:09:00,248 --> 00:09:02,542
HOPEFULLY,
THERE'LL BE A JUDGE OR...

130
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:06,254
SOMEONE ON THAT PROCESSING
STATION WE CAN TALK TO.

131
00:09:06,296 --> 00:09:07,672
AND IF NOT?

132
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:09,841
YOU MIGHT WANT TO MAKE FRIENDS
WITH THAT NAUSICAAN.

133
00:09:09,883 --> 00:09:11,843
[ DOOR OPENS ]

134
00:09:18,392 --> 00:09:20,143
ARE YOU ARCHER?

135
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:23,397
YOU'RE BEING RELEASED.

136
00:09:23,438 --> 00:09:25,606
SHIP'S COMING TO RETRIEVE YOU.

137
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:27,567
NAUSICAAN: RELEASED? WHY?

138
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:29,610
TUCKER: WE'RE NOT CRIMINALS.

139
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:32,864
[ LAUGHTER ]

140
00:09:32,906 --> 00:09:35,575
HOW MUCH DID THEY PAY YOU
TO LET THEM GO?

141
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:36,784
QUIET.

142
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:39,413
I'M INNOCENT, TOO.

143
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:40,705
I'LL PAY YOU.

144
00:09:40,747 --> 00:09:42,582
I SAID QUIET.

145
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:44,376
WE'RE ALL INNOCENT!

146
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:47,712
HOW MUCH?!

147
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:49,423
[ GRUNTS ]

148
00:09:49,464 --> 00:09:50,798
THAT'S ENOUGH!

149
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:55,136
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

150
00:10:18,743 --> 00:10:20,495
PRISONER: RELEASE ME!

151
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:21,746
I CAN HELP YOU!

152
00:10:21,788 --> 00:10:23,915
KEEP STILL! ALL OF YOU.

153
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:26,084
IF YOU WANT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

154
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,053
[ RESTRAINTS CLICK ]

155
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:45,228
[ ALARM BLARING ]

156
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:02,036
[ GRUNTS ]

157
00:11:13,632 --> 00:11:15,800
[ DOOR OPENS ]

158
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:21,889
I TOLD YOU WE NEEDED THE PILOT.

159
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:23,682
HE'S ALIVE.

160
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:26,727
DOES HE LOOK LIKE HE'S IN
ANY CONDITION TO FLY THIS SHIP?

161
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:29,105
HE TRIED TO GET A WEAPON.

162
00:11:29,147 --> 00:11:30,357
JUST WATCH THEM!

163
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:32,484
WHAT ABOUT THE REST OF US?

164
00:11:32,526 --> 00:11:35,487
YOU'LL BE RELEASED SOON ENOUGH.

165
00:11:35,529 --> 00:11:36,737
WHEN?!

166
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:37,989
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

167
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:39,698
BE PATIENT.

168
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:41,493
YOU'LL FIND OUT.

169
00:11:41,535 --> 00:11:44,329
I'M SURE WE'RE ALL GRATEFUL
FOR YOUR COURAGEOUS EFFORT,

170
00:11:44,371 --> 00:11:46,331
BUT WE'VE BEEN IN THESE
RESTRAINTS FOR THREE DAYS.

171
00:11:46,373 --> 00:11:48,458
-COULDN'T YOU JUST --
-QUIET!

172
00:11:49,584 --> 00:11:52,711
I'LL SEE IF I CAN
ACCESS NAVIGATION.

173
00:11:52,753 --> 00:11:54,713
ARCHER: YOU EVER FLY
A WARP SHIP BEFORE?

174
00:11:54,755 --> 00:11:56,550
IT'S HARDER THAN YOU THINK.

175
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:57,842
TUCKER: HE'S RIGHT.

176
00:11:57,884 --> 00:11:59,177
YOU HIT THE WRONG CONTROL,

177
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:01,179
YOU COULD OVERLOAD
THE PLASMA MANIFOLDS

178
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:04,057
OR SHUT DOWN THE ANTIMATTER
CONTAINMENT FIELD.

179
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:07,726
WE'D ALL END UP A CLOUD
OF IONIZED GAS.

180
00:12:07,768 --> 00:12:09,770
YOU'RE A PILOT?

181
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:11,398
A DAMN GOOD ONE.

182
00:12:12,773 --> 00:12:15,235
I'M A SMUGGLER, REMEMBER?

183
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:20,114
COME WITH ME.

184
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:31,750
MY PARTNER'S AN ENGINEER.
I COULD USE HIS HELP.

185
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:34,295
JUST YOU.

186
00:12:38,841 --> 00:12:40,343
[ BEEPING ]

187
00:12:58,236 --> 00:12:59,987
I THOUGHT YOU WERE A PILOT.

188
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:03,324
EVERY SHIP'S DIFFERENT.

189
00:13:03,366 --> 00:13:05,452
JUST GIVE ME SOME TIME.

190
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:16,837
THESE LOOK LIKE
LANDING THRUSTERS.

191
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:19,633
ATTITUDE CONTROL.

192
00:13:19,674 --> 00:13:22,135
WARP STABILIZERS.

193
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:23,886
NAVIGATION?

194
00:13:29,601 --> 00:13:30,977
NAVIGATION.

195
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:34,397
THERE'S A BINARY SYSTEM
4 LIGHT-YEARS FROM HERE.

196
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:41,488
THIS ONE?

197
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:43,156
-SET A COURSE.
-WHICH PLANET?

198
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:45,032
I'LL TELL YOU THAT
WHEN WE GET THERE.

199
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:47,076
WE'RE NOT GONNA GET VERY FAR
IN A STOLEN PRISON TRANSPORT.

200
00:13:47,118 --> 00:13:50,413
JUST GET ME TO THAT SYSTEM.

201
00:13:58,837 --> 00:14:01,549
[ ENGINES WHIRRING ]

202
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:20,652
GUARD: YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENS
IF HE DIES.

203
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,863
IF YOU GET HIM
MEDICAL ATTENTION,

204
00:14:23,904 --> 00:14:26,741
IT'LL WORK IN YOUR FAVOR.

205
00:14:31,329 --> 00:14:35,500
I'LL TELL THE MAGISTRATE
YOU SHOWED COMPASSION.

206
00:14:38,712 --> 00:14:40,547
[ GROANING ]

207
00:14:43,550 --> 00:14:47,554
THE GUARD SAID YOU WERE
GOING TO BE RELEASED.

208
00:14:47,595 --> 00:14:48,971
WHY?

209
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:51,891
BECAUSE WE'RE INNOCENT.

210
00:14:51,932 --> 00:14:56,187
I HAVE FRIENDS WHO WANTED TO
KEEP DOING BUSINESS WITH ME.

211
00:14:56,229 --> 00:14:59,982
THEY MADE A FEW
DISCREET PAYMENTS, AND NOW...

212
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:01,735
I'M INNOCENT.

213
00:15:01,776 --> 00:15:04,987
I WOULD HAVE BEEN
OFF THIS SHIP BY NOW

214
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:07,657
IF YOU HADN'T STAGED
YOUR LITTLE REVOLT.

215
00:15:07,699 --> 00:15:10,159
I HOPE YOU'VE
THOUGHT THIS THROUGH.

216
00:15:10,201 --> 00:15:12,328
EVERY DETAIL.

217
00:15:13,246 --> 00:15:15,498
I'M CURIOUS.

218
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:17,834
HOW'D YOU GET OUT
OF THOSE RESTRAINTS?

219
00:15:19,794 --> 00:15:22,088
YOU COULDN'T HAVE A LOCKPICK.
THE GUARDS WOULD HAVE FOUND IT.

220
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:24,758
WOULD THEY?

221
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,928
SUBDERMAL IMPLANTS.

222
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:31,055
THEY DEPOLARIZE
TRIBURNIUM ALLOYS.

223
00:15:31,097 --> 00:15:33,266
HOW DID YOU KNOW
YOU WERE GOING TO NEED THEM?

224
00:15:33,307 --> 00:15:37,478
I SERVED SEVEN YEARS ON CANAMAR
BEFORE I ESCAPED.

225
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:40,022
I DON'T INTEND TO GO BACK.

226
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:43,067
SO, I LEFT PREPARED.

227
00:15:48,698 --> 00:15:51,910
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'VE GOT
IN MIND, BUT I'M INVOLVED NOW.

228
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:55,246
I DON'T WANT TO GO TO CANAMAR
ANY MORE THAN YOU DO.

229
00:15:55,288 --> 00:15:59,834
IF WE RUN INTO TROUBLE,
MY PARTNER COULD HELP.

230
00:15:59,876 --> 00:16:01,085
WHAT IS THAT?

231
00:16:01,127 --> 00:16:02,879
SUBSPACE TRANSCEIVER.

232
00:16:02,921 --> 00:16:05,131
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT TRYING
TO SEND A MESSAGE.

233
00:16:05,172 --> 00:16:07,675
I'M TAKING IT OFFLINE.

234
00:16:07,717 --> 00:16:11,596
IT LEAVES A SUBSPACE SIGNATURE
EVEN WHEN IT'S NOT TRANSMITTING.

235
00:16:11,638 --> 00:16:13,097
SOMEONE COULD TRACK US.

236
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,646
NOW IT'S OFFLINE.

237
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:32,408
[ BEEPING ]

238
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:35,328
I'M PICKING UP
AN AUTOMATED DISTRESS SIGNAL.

239
00:16:37,872 --> 00:16:39,499
THAT'S ONE OF OUR FREQUENCIES.

240
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,417
YOUR TRANSPORT VESSEL?

241
00:16:41,459 --> 00:16:42,836
WE HAVE HUNDREDS OF SHIPS.

242
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:45,045
I DON'T KNOW THE SIGNATURES
FOR EVERY ONE.

243
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:48,174
THE SIGNAL ORIGINATED NEAR
OUR RENDEZVOUS COORDINATES,

244
00:16:48,215 --> 00:16:51,552
BUT THEY'VE STOPPED
TRANSMITTING.

245
00:16:51,594 --> 00:16:53,387
TRY HAILING THEM.

246
00:16:57,767 --> 00:16:59,393
NO RESPONSE.

247
00:17:00,353 --> 00:17:03,063
INCREASE OUR SPEED TO WARP 4.2.

248
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:04,691
WE'RE STILL SEVERAL HOURS AWAY,

249
00:17:04,732 --> 00:17:07,151
BUT WE HAVE PATROL SHIPS
IN THAT AREA.

250
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:09,946
CONTACT THEM.

251
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:23,918
ZOUMAS: HAVE YOU EVER TRIED
TOJAL?

252
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,127
TUCKER: WHAT?

253
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:26,379
ZOUMAS: THERE'S NOTHING LIKE IT,

254
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:28,006
BUT YOU HAVE TO EAT IT
BEFORE IT COOLS.

255
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,966
-OTHERWISE IT'LL CONGEAL.
-SOUNDS TERRIFIC.

256
00:17:30,008 --> 00:17:32,468
IT'S THE FIRST THING I'M GONNA
HAVE WHEN WE'RE OFF THIS SHIP.

257
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:34,721
WHERE DO YOU THINK
THEY'RE TAKING US?

258
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:36,180
ASK HIM.

259
00:17:37,724 --> 00:17:39,017
I'LL JUST WAIT AND SEE.

260
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:41,519
THE ENOLIANS WON'T
STOP LOOKING FOR US.

261
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:42,896
WE'LL BE FUGITIVES.

262
00:17:42,937 --> 00:17:44,856
I WAS THINKING OF HAVING
MY FACE RECONFIGURED.

263
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:46,524
THERE'S A SURGEON
ON BURALA PRIME WHO CAN DO IT.

264
00:17:46,566 --> 00:17:47,734
HE COULD HELP YOU, AS WELL.

265
00:17:47,775 --> 00:17:49,736
I'LL TAKE MY CHANCES
WITH MY OWN FACE.

266
00:17:49,777 --> 00:17:50,987
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN
TO BURALA PRIME?

267
00:17:51,029 --> 00:17:52,321
CAN'T SAY I HAVE.

268
00:17:52,363 --> 00:17:54,490
IF YOU EVER GO,
AVOID THE POLAR ISLANDS.

269
00:17:54,532 --> 00:17:56,910
THE PEOPLE ARE FRIENDLY,
BUT THE COLD IS UNBEARABLE.
NOTHING BUT ICE AND GLACIERS.

270
00:17:56,951 --> 00:17:58,536
I WAS STRANDED THERE
FOR THREE MONTHS

271
00:17:58,578 --> 00:18:00,371
WHEN SOME COLLEAGUES OF MINE
DECIDED TO LEAVE WITHOUT ME.

272
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:01,581
IMAGINE THAT.

273
00:18:01,622 --> 00:18:03,123
THE DAY I GOT LOST,
THAT WAS THE WORST.

274
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,251
14 HOURS -- IT TOOK ME 14 HOURS

275
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:06,794
TO FIND MY WAY BACK
TO THE OUTPOST.

276
00:18:06,836 --> 00:18:08,212
I LOST THREE TOES TO FROSTBITE.

277
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:09,923
I'VE WALKED WITH A SLIGHT LIMP
EVER SINCE,

278
00:18:09,964 --> 00:18:11,716
NOT THAT YOU'D NOTICE.

279
00:18:11,758 --> 00:18:14,052
I'M GONNA GET THAT SURGEON TO DO
SOME WORK ON MY FOOT, AS WELL.

280
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:15,595
MAYBE HE CAN REPLACE
THE MISSING TOES.

281
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:16,930
EXCUSE ME.

282
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:20,140
CAN I CHANGE SEATS?

283
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:22,560
[ CHUCKLES ]

284
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:28,190
I'M SURPRISED WE HAVEN'T
CROSSED PATHS BEFORE.

285
00:18:29,734 --> 00:18:31,819
WE'RE NEW TO THIS REGION.

286
00:18:31,861 --> 00:18:36,240
WE USED TO WORK MOSTLY
IN THE SOL SYSTEM.

287
00:18:36,282 --> 00:18:37,867
SOL?

288
00:18:37,909 --> 00:18:39,243
IT'S OUR SUN.

289
00:18:39,285 --> 00:18:41,829
OUR HOMEWORLD IS CALLED EARTH.

290
00:18:41,871 --> 00:18:43,289
[ BEEPING ]

291
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:44,999
WHAT IS IT?

292
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:49,045
TWO VESSELS
APPROACHING FROM AFT.

293
00:18:49,087 --> 00:18:50,797
LET ME SEE THEM.

294
00:18:55,301 --> 00:18:57,929
ENOLIAN PATROL SHIPS.

295
00:19:04,018 --> 00:19:05,269
THEY'VE FOUND US.

296
00:19:05,311 --> 00:19:06,771
MORE QUICKLY THAN I EXPECTED.

297
00:19:06,813 --> 00:19:09,148
WHEN YOU WERE TAKING
THE TRANSCEIVER OFFLINE,

298
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:10,650
YOU DIDN'T ACTIVATE IT
ACCIDENTALLY?

299
00:19:10,691 --> 00:19:12,443
YOU THINK I SENT
A DISTRESS CALL?

300
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:14,487
I TOLD YOU WE SHOULD HAVE
GOTTEN RID OF THIS SHIP.

301
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:17,031
IT'S TOO EASY TO TRACK.

302
00:19:17,073 --> 00:19:18,240
[ BEEPING ]

303
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:19,533
THEY'RE CHARGING WEAPONS.

304
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:20,827
DO THE SAME!

305
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:23,162
THOSE ARE HEAVILY ARMED
PATROL SHIPS.

306
00:19:23,203 --> 00:19:24,455
WE'RE ONLY A TRANSPORT.

307
00:19:24,497 --> 00:19:26,165
WE HAVE WEAPONS -- USE THEM!

308
00:19:26,206 --> 00:19:27,625
WE'RE OUTGUNNED!

309
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:30,586
I'D RATHER TAKE MY CHANCES
ON CANAMAR.

310
00:19:30,628 --> 00:19:32,254
AND I'D RATHER NOT.

311
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:34,966
NOW CHARGE THE WEAPONS.

312
00:19:36,676 --> 00:19:38,928
THEY'RE TARGETING OUR ENGINES.

313
00:19:38,970 --> 00:19:40,847
RETURN FIRE!

314
00:19:42,098 --> 00:19:43,265
NO.

315
00:19:43,307 --> 00:19:44,684
I'M WARNING YOU...

316
00:19:44,725 --> 00:19:46,519
WE DON'T HAVE THE FIREPOWER.

317
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:49,897
IF WE ATTACK THOSE SHIPS,
THEY'LL DESTROY US.

318
00:19:49,939 --> 00:19:53,400
I THINK I CAN GET US
OUT OF THIS...

319
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:56,320
BUT I'LL NEED TUCKER'S HELP.

320
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:09,083
[ GRUNTS ]

321
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:10,292
OH!

322
00:20:10,334 --> 00:20:11,919
WHAT'S HAPPENING?!

323
00:20:11,961 --> 00:20:14,630
IF THOSE ARE PATROL SHIPS,
YOU'RE GOING TO BE RECAPTURED.

324
00:20:14,672 --> 00:20:16,632
SHOULDN'T WE BE GETTING
TO THE ESCAPE PODS?

325
00:20:16,674 --> 00:20:19,510
THE NEXT PERSON WHO SPEAKS
GOES OUT THE AIRLOCK!

326
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:22,096
HE NEEDS TO CONCENTRATE.

327
00:20:28,310 --> 00:20:29,562
TRIP, WHAT'S YOUR STATUS?

328
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:31,064
ALMOST THERE!

329
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:37,277
LET US GO! I DON'T WANT TO DIE
TIED UP LIKE AN ANIMAL!

330
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,072
AAH!

331
00:20:39,113 --> 00:20:40,447
[ GROANS ]

332
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:43,743
READY WHEN YOU ARE!

333
00:20:46,746 --> 00:20:49,289
CEASE FIRE!
CEASE FIRE!

334
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:51,084
WE SURRENDER.

335
00:20:56,047 --> 00:20:58,883
Pressurize your docking port
and prepare to be boarded,

336
00:20:58,925 --> 00:21:01,510
or our next shot
will breach your hull.

337
00:21:01,552 --> 00:21:03,846
ACKNOWLEDGED.

338
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,813
NOW!

339
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,400
THE PLASMA VENTS ARE OPEN!

340
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,335
THEY'VE TAKEN DAMAGE.

341
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:36,670
PROPULSION IS DOWN
ON BOTH SHIPS.

342
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:38,047
LOCK WEAPONS.

343
00:21:38,089 --> 00:21:39,506
WE SHOULD GET OUT OF HERE
WHILE WE CAN.

344
00:21:39,548 --> 00:21:41,467
-TARGET THEIR WARP REACTORS!
-THERE'S NO NEED.

345
00:21:41,508 --> 00:21:42,969
AS SOON AS THEY
REPAIR THEIR DAMAGE,

346
00:21:43,010 --> 00:21:44,553
THEY'LL COME AFTER US AGAIN.

347
00:21:44,595 --> 00:21:46,180
DO YOU THINK THE ENOLIANS
ARE JUST GOING TO GIVE UP

348
00:21:46,222 --> 00:21:48,432
IF WE DESTROY
TWO OF THEIR SHIPS?

349
00:21:48,474 --> 00:21:50,268
ALL I'M WANTED FOR IS SMUGGLING.

350
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:52,979
I DON'T NEED TO ADD
MURDER CHARGES TO IT.

351
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:56,065
LET ME GET US OUT OF HERE.

352
00:21:56,107 --> 00:21:57,984
ALL RIGHT.

353
00:22:03,489 --> 00:22:05,407
IS THIS REALLY NECESSARY?

354
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:08,535
I JUST SAVED YOUR SKIN,
AND YOU STILL DON'T TRUST ME?

355
00:22:08,577 --> 00:22:13,499
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH POWER FLOWS
THROUGH THOSE PLASMA CIRCUITS?

356
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:15,168
HOW MUCH?

357
00:22:16,418 --> 00:22:18,171
A LOT.

358
00:22:19,797 --> 00:22:22,216
I COULD HAVE BEEN ELECTROCUTED.

359
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:25,094
AH, THE LEAST YOU COULD DO
IS SAY THANKS.

360
00:22:28,388 --> 00:22:30,266
THANKS.

361
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:35,646
THAT WAS NICE.

362
00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:38,065
IT REMINDS ME
OF THE TIME I WAS --

363
00:22:38,107 --> 00:22:40,193
SHUT UP!

364
00:22:43,445 --> 00:22:47,116
BOTH OUR SHIPS WERE DISABLED
BEFORE THE TRANSPORT ESCAPED.

365
00:22:47,158 --> 00:22:50,368
MY SUPERIORS DON'T WANT OUR
PATROLS TAKING ANY MORE CHANCES.

366
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:54,581
THEY'VE ISSUED ORDERS
TO DESTROY THE PRISON TRANSPORT.

367
00:22:54,623 --> 00:22:56,292
ARE YOUR SUPERIORS AWARE

368
00:22:56,334 --> 00:22:58,336
THAT THERE ARE
TWO INNOCENT HUMANS ABOARD?

369
00:22:58,376 --> 00:23:01,255
THEY'RE MORE CONCERNED WITH
THE MAN WHO PLANNED THIS ESCAPE.

370
00:23:01,297 --> 00:23:02,756
THEY WERE ABLE
TO MATCH HIS VOICE-PRINT

371
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:05,383
TO A PRISONER
NAMED KURODA LOR-EHN.

372
00:23:05,425 --> 00:23:08,679
HE WAS RESPONSIBLE FOR MANY
CRIMES, SOME OF THEM BRUTAL.

373
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:10,264
THEY'RE DETERMINED TO STOP HIM.

374
00:23:10,306 --> 00:23:12,058
AND WE'RE DETERMINED
TO GET OUR PEOPLE BACK.

375
00:23:12,099 --> 00:23:15,477
THEN I SUGGEST YOU FIND THEM
BEFORE OUR PATROLS DO.

376
00:23:21,734 --> 00:23:26,446
THAT WAS A CLEVER TRICK,
IGNITING THE PLASMA.

377
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:29,407
I USED IT ONCE BEFORE...

378
00:23:29,449 --> 00:23:33,079
OUTRUNNING A CUSTOMS VESSEL
NEAR CORIDAN.

379
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:35,915
YOU OBVIOUSLY RAN OUT
OF CLEVER TRICKS.

380
00:23:35,956 --> 00:23:38,167
OTHERWISE YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE.

381
00:23:38,209 --> 00:23:40,086
WHAT HAPPENED?

382
00:23:43,297 --> 00:23:48,219
EVERY SHIP LEAVING KETO-ENOL
WAS BEING BOARDED AND SEARCHED.

383
00:23:48,261 --> 00:23:52,472
TO GET THROUGH THE CHECKPOINT,
I SAID I WAS A STARSHIP CAPTAIN

384
00:23:52,514 --> 00:23:54,850
AND TUCKER WAS MY ENGINEER.

385
00:23:54,892 --> 00:23:56,476
I MADE QUITE A POINT

386
00:23:56,518 --> 00:24:01,439
ABOUT HOW I WAS ON A PEACEFUL
MISSION OF EXPLORATION.

387
00:24:01,481 --> 00:24:03,525
THEY DIDN'T BELIEVE YOU?

388
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:05,819
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

389
00:24:05,861 --> 00:24:09,407
THEY TURNED OUR SHUTTLE
INSIDE OUT...

390
00:24:09,447 --> 00:24:14,494
FOUND MY CARGO,
AND WE WOUND UP HERE.

391
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:16,997
MY GOOD FORTUNE.

392
00:24:17,039 --> 00:24:20,418
YOU SHOULD CONSIDER
COMING WITH US.

393
00:24:20,458 --> 00:24:22,253
YOUR PARTNER, TOO.

394
00:24:22,295 --> 00:24:24,422
DOING WHAT?

395
00:24:24,462 --> 00:24:27,507
I HAVE SOME BUSINESS
I WASN'T ABLE TO FINISH

396
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:29,509
BEFORE I WAS ARRESTED.

397
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:32,763
IT COULD BE PROFITABLE.

398
00:24:32,805 --> 00:24:35,515
I'M A SMUGGLER.

399
00:24:35,557 --> 00:24:37,226
I'M NOT GOOD AT MUCH ELSE.

400
00:24:37,268 --> 00:24:39,937
TRUST ME,
YOU'LL BE VERY INTERESTED

401
00:24:39,979 --> 00:24:43,065
WHEN YOU FIND OUT
WHAT I HAVE IN MIND.

402
00:24:46,484 --> 00:24:50,530
IT'S NOT AS IF I HAVE A LOT
OF OPTIONS RIGHT NOW.

403
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:55,995
BUT IF WE'RE GOING TO
WORK TOGETHER...

404
00:24:56,036 --> 00:24:58,538
I'D LIKE TO KNOW
WHERE WE'RE HEADED.

405
00:24:58,580 --> 00:25:00,333
THE FOURTH PLANET.

406
00:25:00,374 --> 00:25:03,002
THERE'S A TRADING OUTPOST
CALLED TAMAAL.

407
00:25:03,043 --> 00:25:04,211
AND THEN?

408
00:25:04,253 --> 00:25:06,797
A SHIP'S GOING TO MEET US THERE.

409
00:25:06,839 --> 00:25:11,802
THIS TRANSPORT
DRAWS TOO MUCH ATTENTION.

410
00:25:13,929 --> 00:25:15,139
ZOUMAS: ONCE YOU GET PAST
THE TEXTURE,

411
00:25:15,181 --> 00:25:16,598
THEY REALLY
DON'T TASTE THAT BAD.

412
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,184
THE FUN PART IS KEEPING THEM
IN YOUR MOUTH.

413
00:25:18,225 --> 00:25:19,726
THEY JUMP AROUND UNTIL YOU
CRUNCH DOWN ON THEM --

414
00:25:19,768 --> 00:25:21,561
ENOUGH!

415
00:25:21,603 --> 00:25:23,189
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

416
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:26,524
NO. I LOVE HEARING HOW DELICIOUS
MELVARAN MUD FLEAS ARE

417
00:25:26,566 --> 00:25:29,820
OR ABOUT THE TIME YOU SPENT TWO
HOURS WITH AN ORION SLAVE GIRL

418
00:25:29,862 --> 00:25:31,780
OR THE MIRACLES DOCTORS
CAN PERFORM THESE DAYS,

419
00:25:31,822 --> 00:25:33,324
GETTING RID OF FLUVIAN FUNGUS.

420
00:25:33,366 --> 00:25:34,950
WELL, WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
I WANT TO HEAR<i> YOUR</i> STORIES?

421
00:25:34,992 --> 00:25:36,327
I HAVEN'T TOLD YOU ANY!

422
00:25:36,369 --> 00:25:38,162
YOU WON'T LET ME
GET A WORD IN EDGEWISE!

423
00:25:38,204 --> 00:25:41,457
I CAN'T EVEN PUT MY FINGERS
IN MY EARS.

424
00:25:41,499 --> 00:25:44,168
10 MINUTES --
THAT'S ALL I'M ASKING.

425
00:25:44,210 --> 00:25:47,296
JUST 10 MINUTES OF SILENCE.

426
00:25:47,338 --> 00:25:51,342
I DIDN'T REALIZE
I WAS BEING SO ANNOYING.

427
00:25:51,384 --> 00:25:53,802
WE SEEMED TO BE
GETTING ALONG SO WELL.

428
00:25:53,844 --> 00:25:57,139
I JUST THOUGHT IT MIGHT BE NICE
TO HAVE A PLEASANT CONVERSATION

429
00:25:57,181 --> 00:26:00,934
BEFORE I SPEND THE NEXT 10 YEARS
ON A PENAL COLONY.

430
00:26:05,523 --> 00:26:07,565
LOOK...

431
00:26:07,607 --> 00:26:11,904
I'M SORRY I SNAPPED AT YOU.

432
00:26:11,945 --> 00:26:16,867
BUT THIS ISN'T EXACTLY
THE BEST PLACE TO SOCIALIZE.

433
00:26:22,873 --> 00:26:25,167
THIS THRUSTER ASSEMBLY
TOOK A LOT OF DAMAGE.

434
00:26:25,209 --> 00:26:27,627
WE SHOULD HAVE TUCKER
TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

435
00:26:27,669 --> 00:26:29,004
DON'T BOTHER.

436
00:26:29,046 --> 00:26:31,965
YOU'RE NOT THE ONE
WHO HAS TO FLY THIS THING.

437
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:34,760
IT WON'T BE FLYING MUCH LONGER.

438
00:26:34,801 --> 00:26:36,636
[ DOOR OPENS ]

439
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:40,433
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

440
00:26:40,474 --> 00:26:42,642
YOU HAVEN'T EATEN FOR TWO DAYS.

441
00:26:42,684 --> 00:26:44,437
I CAN WAIT.

442
00:26:44,478 --> 00:26:45,979
DON'T BE A FOOL.

443
00:26:46,021 --> 00:26:48,690
I SAID I'M NOT HUNGRY!

444
00:26:53,653 --> 00:26:55,489
[ DOOR OPENS ]

445
00:26:57,450 --> 00:27:00,244
PRISON RATIONS!

446
00:27:01,954 --> 00:27:03,621
IT'S BETTER THAN NOTHING.

447
00:27:03,663 --> 00:27:06,959
YOU OBVIOUSLY NEVER SPENT TIME
ON A PENAL COLONY.

448
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:10,837
I WAS 14 WHEN I FIRST
TASTED THOSE RATIONS.

449
00:27:10,879 --> 00:27:15,050
I'VE HAD ENOUGH
FOR ONE LIFETIME.

450
00:27:19,263 --> 00:27:24,684
SOUNDS LIKE YOU STARTED
YOUR CAREER EARLY.

451
00:27:24,726 --> 00:27:27,104
I WAS YOUNG.

452
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:31,484
BUT I WAS NO CRIMINAL.

453
00:27:31,525 --> 00:27:33,319
NO?

454
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:36,405
MY FATHER AND I WERE WORKING AT
A TRANSPORT YARD ON KETO-ENOL.

455
00:27:36,447 --> 00:27:40,117
THE SUPERVISOR ACCUSED ME
OF STEALING A BRACE OF LATINUM.

456
00:27:40,159 --> 00:27:41,619
I HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH IT,

457
00:27:41,659 --> 00:27:45,289
BUT THEY COULDN'T FIND
ANYONE ELSE TO BLAME.

458
00:27:45,331 --> 00:27:50,043
I WAS SENTENCED
TO FIVE YEARS AT DURONOM.

459
00:27:53,964 --> 00:27:55,841
THAT SOUNDS PRETTY SEVERE.

460
00:27:55,882 --> 00:27:58,844
ENOLIAN GUARDS ARE KNOWN
FOR THEIR SEVERITY.

461
00:27:58,885 --> 00:28:00,638
HAVEN'T YOU SEEN THAT BY NOW?

462
00:28:00,678 --> 00:28:02,014
[ CHUCKLES ]

463
00:28:02,055 --> 00:28:04,933
I LEARNED FAR MORE IN PRISON

464
00:28:04,975 --> 00:28:07,685
THAN MY FATHER
COULD HAVE EVER TAUGHT ME.

465
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:12,858
AFTER I WAS RELEASED, I CHOSE
TO PUT MY NEW SKILLS TO USE.

466
00:28:12,899 --> 00:28:16,987
I SUPPOSE I SHOULD BE GRATEFUL.

467
00:28:17,029 --> 00:28:19,448
IF IT WASN'T
FOR THE ENOLIAN GUARD,

468
00:28:19,490 --> 00:28:24,244
MY LIFE...WOULD HAVE BEEN
QUITE DULL.

469
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:41,761
WELCOME TO TAMAAL.

470
00:28:41,803 --> 00:28:44,598
WHERE ARE YOUR FRIENDS?

471
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:46,392
THEY'LL BE HERE.

472
00:28:46,433 --> 00:28:49,186
DO YOU HAVE LANDING COORDINATES?

473
00:28:49,228 --> 00:28:51,188
WE'RE NOT LANDING.

474
00:28:52,814 --> 00:28:54,650
THEY'RE GOING TO DOCK WITH US.

475
00:28:56,735 --> 00:28:58,571
WHAT ABOUT THE OTHERS?

476
00:28:58,612 --> 00:29:00,822
ARE YOU GOING TO LET THEM
GO TO PRISON?

477
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:02,866
NO.

478
00:29:05,827 --> 00:29:07,287
BEFORE WE LEAVE,

479
00:29:07,329 --> 00:29:10,874
YOU'RE GOING TO SET THIS SHIP
ON A DECAYING ORBIT.

480
00:29:13,293 --> 00:29:15,170
IT'LL BE INCINERATED.

481
00:29:15,212 --> 00:29:17,797
AS FAR AS ANYONE
WILL BE ABLE TO TELL,

482
00:29:17,839 --> 00:29:19,508
WE CRASHED TRYING TO LAND.

483
00:29:21,427 --> 00:29:24,888
WHY KILL ALL THESE PEOPLE?
JUST LEAVE THEM.

484
00:29:24,930 --> 00:29:28,392
NO ONE WILL BE LOOKING FOR US
IF THEY THINK WE'RE DEAD.

485
00:29:30,477 --> 00:29:34,356
IF YOU DON'T LIKE IT, YOU CAN
ALWAYS GO BACK TO YOUR SEAT.

486
00:29:34,398 --> 00:29:36,734
I MAY NOT KNOW
HOW TO FLY THIS SHIP,

487
00:29:36,775 --> 00:29:39,903
BUT I'M SURE I CAN FIGURE OUT
HOW TO CRASH IT.

488
00:29:57,588 --> 00:29:58,797
[ BEEPING ]

489
00:29:58,838 --> 00:30:00,299
THE TRANSPORT'S
DROPPED OUT OF WARP.

490
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:02,509
IT'S ENTERED A BINARY SYSTEM.

491
00:30:02,551 --> 00:30:05,262
IT LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE HEADING
FOR THE FOURTH PLANET.

492
00:30:05,304 --> 00:30:07,847
ENOLIAN: TAMAAL --
IT'S A LARGE TRADING OUTPOST

493
00:30:07,889 --> 00:30:09,849
WITH OVER TWO MILLION
INHABITANTS.

494
00:30:09,891 --> 00:30:12,894
REED: A GOOD PLACE
TO GET LOST IN THE CROWD.

495
00:30:14,896 --> 00:30:16,982
DROP TO IMPULSE.

496
00:30:17,023 --> 00:30:19,610
TAKE US INTO THE SYSTEM.

497
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:23,697
ANY HUMAN BIOSIGNS?

498
00:30:23,739 --> 00:30:25,699
TWO. IT'S THEM.

499
00:30:25,741 --> 00:30:28,327
I RECOMMEND WE USE THE
TRANSPORTER ONCE WE'RE IN RANGE.

500
00:30:28,368 --> 00:30:30,120
YOU'RE FORGETTING
THAT'S A PRISON SHIP.

501
00:30:30,162 --> 00:30:31,789
IT'S HEAVILY SHIELDED.

502
00:30:40,922 --> 00:30:42,299
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

503
00:30:42,341 --> 00:30:45,844
THE DOCKING HATCH WAS DAMAGED
BY THE PATROL SHIPS.

504
00:30:45,885 --> 00:30:49,389
KURODA WANTS TUCKER
TO SEE IF HE CAN REPAIR IT.

505
00:30:59,232 --> 00:31:00,984
NICE OF YOU TO VISIT.

506
00:31:01,026 --> 00:31:02,902
WHO ARE WE DOCKING WITH?

507
00:31:02,944 --> 00:31:05,113
YOUR GUESS IS AS GOOD AS MINE.

508
00:31:10,994 --> 00:31:13,079
HE'S TAKING US OFF ON A SHUTTLE.

509
00:31:13,121 --> 00:31:15,040
THEN HE PLANS TO CRASH THE SHIP.

510
00:31:15,081 --> 00:31:17,083
I HOPE YOU'VE GOT
SOMETHING ELSE IN MIND.

511
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:18,918
WE CAN'T WAIT FOR<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

512
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:21,505
WE'VE GOT TO TRY
TO TAKE CONTROL.

513
00:31:22,964 --> 00:31:25,008
THINK YOU CAN HANDLE HIM?

514
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:29,805
YEAH, PIECE OF CAKE.

515
00:31:29,847 --> 00:31:31,306
[ BEEPING ]

516
00:31:31,348 --> 00:31:33,559
THERE'S A SMALL VESSEL
DROPPING OUT OF WARP.

517
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:34,893
PATROL SHIP?

518
00:31:34,934 --> 00:31:36,269
REED: I DON'T THINK SO.

519
00:31:36,311 --> 00:31:38,397
FOUR BIOSIGNS.
THEY'RE ALL ENOLIAN.

520
00:31:38,438 --> 00:31:41,233
IT'S NOT ONE OF OUR SHIPS.

521
00:31:41,274 --> 00:31:43,652
MAGNIFY.

522
00:31:44,944 --> 00:31:46,279
WHERE'S IT HEADING?

523
00:31:46,321 --> 00:31:48,574
THE FOURTH PLANET.

524
00:31:48,615 --> 00:31:51,117
HOSHI: THEY'RE TRYING TO HAIL
THE PRISON TRANSPORT.

525
00:31:51,159 --> 00:31:54,329
THEY'RE NOT GETTING A RESPONSE.

526
00:31:56,956 --> 00:32:00,711
THEY MAY HAVE COME
TO RESCUE KURODA.

527
00:32:02,379 --> 00:32:04,130
HOW HEAVILY ARMED IS IT?

528
00:32:04,172 --> 00:32:07,634
FORE AND AFT PARTICLE CANNONS --
NOTHING WE CAN'T HANDLE.

529
00:32:17,436 --> 00:32:19,855
MY FRIENDS WILL BE HERE SOON.

530
00:32:19,897 --> 00:32:21,981
LAY IN A DESCENT COURSE.

531
00:32:23,734 --> 00:32:26,945
THEIR SHIP MIGHT BE BIG ENOUGH
TO HOLD EVERYONE HERE.

532
00:32:26,986 --> 00:32:28,238
WHY DON'T WE TAKE THEM ALONG?

533
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:31,032
WE HAVE ALREADY DISCUSSED THIS!

534
00:32:41,501 --> 00:32:42,669
TRIP...

535
00:32:42,711 --> 00:32:45,046
how's that docking port coming?

536
00:32:45,088 --> 00:32:47,006
[ GRUNTS ]

537
00:32:47,048 --> 00:32:49,384
[ PANTING ]

538
00:32:49,426 --> 00:32:51,136
I NEED A MINUTE.

539
00:32:51,177 --> 00:32:52,387
[ SIGHS ]

540
00:32:52,429 --> 00:32:54,013
IT'S A BIG JOB.

541
00:32:54,055 --> 00:32:57,016
DO YOUR BEST.

542
00:32:57,058 --> 00:32:58,644
[ SIGHS ]

543
00:32:58,685 --> 00:33:02,021
LISTEN...I KNOW WE KIND OF
GOT OFF ON THE WRONG FOOT.

544
00:33:02,063 --> 00:33:03,607
NO HARD FEELINGS.

545
00:33:03,649 --> 00:33:06,985
BUT NOW THAT WE'RE FRIENDS,
I COULD USE A HAND.

546
00:33:07,026 --> 00:33:10,029
YOU'RE THE ENGINEER.

547
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:11,615
TRUE.

548
00:33:11,657 --> 00:33:14,242
BUT I'M HAVING TROUBLE
GETTING THE INTAKE VALVE OPEN.

549
00:33:14,284 --> 00:33:16,912
I GUESS I DON'T HAVE
THE MUSCLE FOR IT.

550
00:33:16,954 --> 00:33:22,041
UNLESS I'M MISTAKEN, KURODA
WANTS THIS HATCH REPAIRED.

551
00:33:26,964 --> 00:33:31,760
THAT ONE -- IF YOU COULD
TURN IT COUNTERCLOCKWISE.

552
00:33:33,470 --> 00:33:35,722
DOWN A LITTLE MORE.

553
00:33:35,764 --> 00:33:38,767
IT'S GOT TO GO
AT LEAST 90 DEGREES.

554
00:33:38,809 --> 00:33:42,020
[ GRUNTING ]

555
00:33:42,061 --> 00:33:44,063
THAT'S IT.

556
00:33:44,105 --> 00:33:46,232
[ GRUNTING ]

557
00:33:46,274 --> 00:33:48,735
YOU ALMOST GOT IT.

558
00:33:52,071 --> 00:33:53,490
PRISONER:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

559
00:33:53,532 --> 00:33:55,241
ZOUMAS: THEY SAID
THEY WERE GOING TO LET US GO!

560
00:33:55,283 --> 00:33:57,160
THEY LIED. THEY'RE PLANNING
TO KILL YOU -- ALL OF YOU.

561
00:33:57,202 --> 00:33:58,453
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

562
00:33:58,495 --> 00:34:00,079
YOU'RE GOING TO GET US
SENT TO CANAMAR!

563
00:34:00,121 --> 00:34:02,123
KEEP IT DOWN!

564
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:05,794
[ ALARM BLARING ]

565
00:34:05,836 --> 00:34:07,462
STAY HERE.

566
00:34:11,299 --> 00:34:12,634
WATCH OUT!

567
00:34:22,895 --> 00:34:25,230
DO YOU KNOW HOW TO REPAIR
THAT DOCKING HATCH?

568
00:34:25,271 --> 00:34:26,690
IT'S NOT EASY.

569
00:34:28,107 --> 00:34:30,819
WE'RE IN A DECAYING ORBIT!

570
00:34:30,861 --> 00:34:33,030
SHOOT ME, AND YOU'LL DIE
WITH THE OTHERS.

571
00:34:39,160 --> 00:34:40,829
GET TO WORK.

572
00:34:42,581 --> 00:34:44,666
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
KILL THESE PEOPLE.

573
00:34:44,708 --> 00:34:46,084
MOVE!

574
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:58,555
[ GROANING ]

575
00:35:04,269 --> 00:35:07,313
YOU SHOULD THANK ME.

576
00:35:07,355 --> 00:35:09,608
WHAT?

577
00:35:11,234 --> 00:35:12,778
WHERE'S ARCHER?

578
00:35:12,819 --> 00:35:14,863
HE'S WITH THEM,
REPAIRING THE DOCKING HATCH.

579
00:35:14,905 --> 00:35:17,323
THEY SAID THERE'S A SHUTTLE
COMING FOR US.

580
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:19,743
I'M SORRY I HAD TO INTERVENE,

581
00:35:19,785 --> 00:35:21,745
BUT YOU DIDN'T GIVE ME
MUCH CHOICE.

582
00:35:21,787 --> 00:35:23,162
YOU'RE LUCKY
THEY DIDN'T KILL YOU.

583
00:35:23,204 --> 00:35:25,040
KURODA WAS FURIOUS.

584
00:35:25,082 --> 00:35:28,835
BUT EVERYTHING'S FINE NOW.
THEY'RE GOING TO SET US FREE.

585
00:35:30,169 --> 00:35:32,171
YOU'RE WELCOME.

586
00:35:32,213 --> 00:35:34,549
[ RUMBLING ]

587
00:35:37,510 --> 00:35:39,471
THEY'VE DOCKED.

588
00:35:54,193 --> 00:35:55,654
[ DOOR OPENS ]

589
00:36:25,058 --> 00:36:27,185
AAH!

590
00:36:38,655 --> 00:36:40,239
I SEE MY MESSAGE GOT THROUGH.

591
00:36:40,281 --> 00:36:41,491
LOUD AND CLEAR, SIR.

592
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:42,742
CAPTAIN?

593
00:36:42,784 --> 00:36:43,910
WOULD YOU MIND?

594
00:36:43,952 --> 00:36:45,578
WHO<i> ARE</i> THESE PEOPLE?

595
00:36:49,666 --> 00:36:51,835
THIS WILL OPEN THE RESTRAINTS.

596
00:36:55,296 --> 00:36:57,256
GET EVERYONE ON THAT SHUTTLE!

597
00:37:11,396 --> 00:37:14,315
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

598
00:37:14,357 --> 00:37:15,817
FREE ME.

599
00:37:20,780 --> 00:37:22,074
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

600
00:37:22,115 --> 00:37:23,324
COME ON!
COME ON!

601
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:25,160
-KEEP MOVING!
-COME ON!

602
00:37:25,202 --> 00:37:27,037
LET'S GO. LET'S GO.
WE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

603
00:37:27,079 --> 00:37:29,873
LET'S GO, EVERYBODY.
COME ON. MOVE OUT, MOVE OUT.

604
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,168
GO!

605
00:37:33,210 --> 00:37:35,170
GO, GO<i> NOW!</i>

606
00:37:35,212 --> 00:37:36,546
LET'S GO!

607
00:37:38,673 --> 00:37:41,176
DON'T LEAVE ANYONE BEHIND.

608
00:37:46,639 --> 00:37:49,142
GO, GO, GO.
COME ON.

609
00:37:49,184 --> 00:37:50,393
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

610
00:37:50,435 --> 00:37:52,145
[ BEEPING ]

611
00:37:52,187 --> 00:37:53,521
ANYTHING I CAN DO?

612
00:37:53,563 --> 00:37:55,273
UNLESS YOU HAVE
A SPARE THRUSTER ASSEMBLY.

613
00:37:55,314 --> 00:37:57,776
-IS EVERYONE OFF?
-JUST ABOUT.

614
00:37:57,817 --> 00:37:59,569
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

615
00:38:13,208 --> 00:38:14,876
CAPTAIN!

616
00:38:14,918 --> 00:38:16,836
TRAVIS SAYS HE CAN'T MAINTAIN
THE DOCKING SEAL MUCH LONGER.

617
00:38:16,878 --> 00:38:19,131
HE WON'T HAVE TO!
LET'S GO!

618
00:38:28,098 --> 00:38:29,808
[ GRUNTS ]

619
00:38:40,318 --> 00:38:41,945
WE NEED TO BREAK ORBIT!

620
00:38:41,987 --> 00:38:44,281
IT'S TOO LATE!
WE'VE LOST THRUSTERS!

621
00:38:44,322 --> 00:38:46,407
YOU'RE LYING!

622
00:38:47,951 --> 00:38:49,410
WE'VE GOT TO GET OUT!

623
00:39:49,804 --> 00:39:51,973
[ SCREAMS ]

624
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:04,903
KURODA!

625
00:40:06,279 --> 00:40:07,488
IT'S OVER!

626
00:40:07,530 --> 00:40:10,200
I WON'T GO BACK!

627
00:40:13,411 --> 00:40:15,038
IT'S NOW OR NEVER, SIR!

628
00:40:36,559 --> 00:40:38,895
[ PANTING ]

629
00:40:42,565 --> 00:40:45,026
[ ALARM BLARING ]

630
00:41:05,463 --> 00:41:08,007
WE'VE GOT SOME MEN IN THERE
WHO COULD USE YOUR HELP.

631
00:41:08,049 --> 00:41:09,801
-AND YOU?
-I'LL BE FINE.

632
00:41:09,842 --> 00:41:11,428
ON BEHALF
OF THE ENOLIAN GOVERNMENT,

633
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:14,973
I'D LIKE TO EXTEND OUR APOLOGIES
FOR THIS INCONVENIENCE.

634
00:41:15,014 --> 00:41:16,224
MY SUPERIORS WILL WANT --

635
00:41:16,266 --> 00:41:18,351
TRIP.

636
00:41:18,393 --> 00:41:19,852
UH, CAPTAIN...

637
00:41:21,771 --> 00:41:24,816
CAPTAIN, MY SUPERIORS WILL WANT
A REPORT ON WHAT HAPPENED.

638
00:41:24,857 --> 00:41:26,484
I'LL GIVE YOU ONE RIGHT NOW.

639
00:41:26,525 --> 00:41:28,445
KURODA'S DEAD, THE OTHER
11 PRISONERS ARE UNDER GUARD.

640
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:31,614
AS YOU'RE AWARE, MY ENGINEER
AND I WERE FALSELY ARRESTED.

641
00:41:31,656 --> 00:41:33,283
WE ALMOST WOUND UP IN CANAMAR.

642
00:41:33,325 --> 00:41:35,493
MAKES ME WONDER HOW MANY OTHERS
DON'T BELONG THERE.

643
00:41:35,534 --> 00:41:37,996
YOU WANTED A REPORT?

644
00:41:38,037 --> 00:41:39,998
YOU'VE GOT ONE.
